job_description:
Business Analyst Client Monitoring
At a glance

Based on our purpose 'Banking for better, for generations to come', we are committed to a sustainable, stable and secure financial system. Detecting financial crime is therefore high on our agenda. This is not new to you, because you follow the news, are broadly interested and socially involved. You want the right thing for customers, society and the bank. That's what you go for! For the CAAP RB-OPS team we are looking for a tech savvy, growth hacking and experienced Business Developer that can help us to scale up with new projects.
Your job

As a Business Developer for the CAAP RB-OPS, which means the Rule Based Operations team on the Client due diligence Advanced Analytics Platform, you are the linking pin between the Business and IT. You will be responsible to kickstart new projects, rule sets and data science models via the lean startup method and discuss with stakeholders their needs and requirements. You know how to sharpen business processes and translate them to IT relatable epics and user stories to put on the Product Backlog.
A Business Developer from the CAAP team strives for structural solutions and quick fixes on the short term. Since CAAP and DFC have a variety of solutions, it is of great importance to have a broad overview and good understanding of what piece of the business process they fulfil, what they deliver and how they interrelate, so that optimal improvements can be provided to stakeholders.
Working environment

The Detecting Financial Crime Grid is responsible for developing and managing the CDD/KYC processes and applications within the bank. The Grid consists of value delivery blocks in the field of Client Acceptance, Client Filtering, Transaction Filtering, Transaction Monitoring, Robotics, Case Management, Business Intelligence and Advanced Analytics. The CAAP Rule Based Operations team is one of the innovative services within DFC. As a piece of the broader CAAP platform, CAAP RBOPS is concerned with triggering systems for state of the art Client and Transaction Monitoring. Replacing manual work, with sophisticated IT solutions, rule sets and data science.
As Business Developer of CAAP RB-OPS you report to the Lead Product Owner of CAAP and you mainly perform your work with the development team; with the Product Owner, Business Developers, IT Engineers and Data Scientists. The development team consists of employees in the Netherlands where Dutch and English are both the communicating language. You also work a lot with other teams within and outside of the DFC Grid, Operational stakeholders and Innovation & Design departments.
We are offering

As an employee of DFC you will land in a developing environment in which hard work is done on a shared vision and objective. You’ll have:
Option to have a 36 hours working week.
A benefit budget of 11%, with which you can buy flexible employment conditions such as extra vacation days. You can also have the benefit budget paid out;
25 vacation days per year;
A personal development budget of € 1,000 per year;
An annual public transport subscription or travel allowance;
A good pension scheme;
Flexible working. A mix between working at the office and from home;
We help you to stay fit & vital.
You help to build our new department. We offer you the freedom to get the best out of yourself with enthusiastic colleagues, to work flexibly and to constantly improve yourself. We believe that both personal and substantive (further) growth is important within DFC.
Your profile

You embody a responsible attitude in your professional manner: you take on activities and make them happen and you help others to be successful. You enjoy a growth mindset.
Skills:
HBO Bachelor or HBO/WO Bachelor's or Master's degree;
At least 5 years of relevant work experience in business development/experiment design/growth hacking, preferably consultancy and Finance/banking;
You have an affinity with IT and an understanding of the possibilities and challenges in the field of automation, data analysis and digitization;
You know how to translate needs of stakeholders to functionalities
You can lead more complex processes and have strong analytical skills;
You have experience with Python/PySpark
You embrace the agile way of working and the lean startup method;
You master English language skills at a business level and good communication skills, both verbal and in writing.
Interested?

Please apply online! For more information, you can contact Jurriaan Amesz via jurriaan.amesz@nl.abnamro.com
Disclaimer external recruitment agencies

External recruitment agencies need to have a signed agreement with ABN AMRO BANK N.V., executed by a Talent Acquisition Specialist, when submitting a resume to a vacancy. In addition, a recruitment agency can only submit a resume when invited by a Talent Acquisition Specialist to join the search for a right candidate. All unsolicited resumes sent to us will be considered property of ABN AMRO BANK N.V. In this case, ABN AMRO will not be held liable to pay a placement fee.

This is what the job entails
As data governance and protection specialist, it is your responsibility to propagate ING’s data strategy across ING. You will further:
expand, improve and actively promote the data management strategy and particularly the data governance aspects;
be responsible for establishing controls around our various policies (on data management, data protection, data retention & deletion and many more) and drive improvements of these controls;
ensure that ING complies with data related policies, standards, roles and responsibilities defined at ING Group level and by our regulators (e.g. GDPR, BCBS239, ESG);
translate policies and guidelines into actionable data governance activities (e.g. data exchanges, data traceability and data quality);
guide and coach others in the field of data management (e.g. data stewards). You bring data literacy into ING!
As data governance and protection specialist you bring with you
As data governance and protection specialist you bring data management experience and enthusiasm around data to ING. You further have:
a passion for data and data governance;
a master’s degree, preferably with a data (governance) background or in law / regulations / accountancy / IT and/or knowledge of DAMA-DMBOK;
a minimum of 5 years’ experience in an area as mentioned above;
the capability to master complex materials and translate them into understandable content;
an excellent understanding of the English language; understanding of Dutch or Romanian is a plus;
an outgoing personality; you can connect with many stakeholders and liaise easily;
a self-starter mentality. A half word is enough to get you going!
This is who we are
ING’s strategy is built around our purpose: Empowering people to stay ahead in life and in business. We want to make the difference for people and the planet by providing a superior customer experience and putting sustainability at the heart of what we do.
In order to make this happen, we need good quality data. Data about customers, products, agreements, transactions and operations. In ING’s CDMO (Chief Data Management Office) organization, data is our heart. We ensure the bank can use data for decisions, reporting, analytics, modelling and much more because the data is of good quality, is managed well throughout the bank and that uniform policies and processes around our data apply. CDMO is a global organization, with people working in Amsterdam, Manilla, Bucharest and many more ING countries.
We are with around 200 data management professionals working on our ambition: making sure data is being treated in a pragmatic, compliant and ethical way! This vacancy is in the Data Governance team. We are with 24 Data Governance enthusiasts, working on nice challenges day in and out.
This is what we offer you
a competitive salary;
a pension scheme, 13th month salary, Individual Savings Contribution being 3.5% of your gross annual salary, 8% holiday payment and a mobility card;
a 36-hour working week and around 25 vacation days (depending on your actual working hours);
office days in our beautiful Cedar office in Amsterdam, flexible working hours as well as remote work options;
How to apply
Ready to apply? Use the link below to upload your motivation letter and CV. If successful, you will be invited to two interviews so we can get to know you as a potential new colleague, and you can get to know us as a potential employer.
We look forward to meeting you! We will close the vacancy at 28/2/2023
